<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14755] Reinstate repaired data tracking when ReadRepair == NONE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14755</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some of the refactoring in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14698&quot; title=&quot;Clean up repair path after Transient Replication &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-14698&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-14698&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; breaks repaired data tracking when read repair is disabled as it skips wrapping the &lt;tt&gt;MergeIterator&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;DataResolver::wrapMergeListener&lt;/tt&gt;. If repaired tracking is enabled, the iterator still needs to be extended so that it calls &lt;tt&gt;RepairedDataTracker::verify&lt;/tt&gt; on close. This wasn&apos;t easy to spot as the new dtests for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14145&quot; title=&quot; Detecting data resurrection during read&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-14145&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-14145&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; haven&apos;t yet been merged. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13185490">CASSANDRA-14755</key>
            <summary>Reinstate repaired data tracking when ReadRepair == NONE</summary>
